Hakeem Kuta, 17, fell six stories from the roof of the Bronx building on Thursday night .
Police were responding to complaints of a group of teens smoking marijuana and loitering in the lobby of the building .
Kuta and five others ran when police arrived and Kuta and his friend were pinned in by a dividing wall .
He died around 11am on Saturday morning after succumbing to the fall .
His father Munir Kuta said his son stayed out of trouble and does not do drugs .